# Debian Package Version Bump

When creating or rebuilding a `.deb` package in this repository:

- Increment the Debian revision every time (e.g. `5.1.4-4` -> `5.1.4-5`).
- Keep `packaging/debian/control` and `packaging/build-deb.sh` versions in sync.
- Never reuse the same package version for a new build that contains changes.
- Before finalizing, verify the built package metadata with:
  - `dpkg-deb -I <path-to-deb>`

Example:

- `packaging/debian/control`: `Version: 5.1.4-5`
- `packaging/build-deb.sh`: `VERSION="5.1.4-5"`
